205namespace WebCore {
206static String convertEnumerationToString(AVPlayerTimeControlStatus enumerationValue)
207{
208 static const NeverDestroyed<String> values[] = {
209 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("AVPlayerTimeControlStatusPaused"),
210 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("AVPlayerTimeControlStatusWaitingToPlayAtSpecifiedRate"),
211 MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("AVPlayerTimeControlStatusPlaying"),
212 };
213 static_assert(!static_cast<size_t>(AVPlayerTimeControlStatusPaused), "AVPlayerTimeControlStatusPaused is not 0 as expected");
214 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(AVPlayerTimeControlStatusWaitingToPlayAtSpecifiedRate) == 1, "AVPlayerTimeControlStatusWaitingToPlayAtSpecifiedRate is not 1 as expected");
215 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(AVPlayerTimeControlStatusPlaying) == 2, "AVPlayerTimeControlStatusPlaying is not 2 as expected");
216 ASSERT(static_cast<size_t>(enumerationValue) < WTF_ARRAY_LENGTH(values));
217 return values[static_cast<size_t>(enumerationValue)];
218}
219}

226struct LogArgument<AVPlayerTimeControlStatus> {
227 static String toString(const AVPlayerTimeControlStatus status)

229 return convertEnumerationToString(status);
230 }

332static AVAssetCache *assetCacheForPath(const String& path)
333{
334 if (path.isEmpty())
335 return nil;
336
337 return [PAL::getAVAssetCacheClass() assetCacheWithURL:[NSURL fileURLWithPath:path isDirectory:YES]];
338}
339
340static AVAssetCache *ensureAssetCacheExistsForPath(const String& path)
341{
342 if (path.isEmpty())
343 return nil;
344
345 auto fileType = FileSystem::fileTypeFollowingSymlinks(path);
346 if (fileType && *fileType != FileSystem::FileType::Directory) {
347 // Non-directory file already exists at the path location; bail.
348 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
349 return nil;
350 }
351
352 if (!fileType && !FileSystem::makeAllDirectories(path)) {
353 // Could not create a directory at the specified location; bail.
354 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
355 return nil;
356 }
357
358 return assetCacheForPath(path);
359}
360
361HashSet<SecurityOriginData> MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::originsInMediaCache(const String& path)
362{
363 HashSet<SecurityOriginData> origins;
364 AVAssetCache* assetCache = assetCacheForPath(path);
365 if (!assetCache)
366 return origins;
367
368 for (NSString *key in [assetCache allKeys]) {
369 URL keyAsURL = URL(URL(), key);
370 if (keyAsURL.isValid())
371 origins.add(SecurityOriginData::fromURL(keyAsURL));
372 }
373 return origins;
374}
375
376static WallTime toSystemClockTime(NSDate *date)
377{
378 ASSERT(date);
379 return WallTime::fromRawSeconds(date.timeIntervalSince1970);
380}
381
382void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::clearMediaCache(const String& path, WallTime modifiedSince)
383{
384 AVAssetCache* assetCache = assetCacheForPath(path);
385 if (!assetCache)
386 return;
387
388 for (NSString *key in [assetCache allKeys]) {
389 if (toSystemClockTime([assetCache lastModifiedDateOfEntryForKey:key]) > modifiedSince)
390 [assetCache removeEntryForKey:key];
391 }
392
393 NSFileManager *fileManager = [NSFileManager defaultManager];
394 NSURL *baseURL = [assetCache URL];
395
396 if (modifiedSince <= WallTime::fromRawSeconds(0)) {
397 [fileManager removeItemAtURL:baseURL error:nil];
398 return;
399 }
400
401 NSArray *propertyKeys = @[NSURLNameKey, NSURLContentModificationDateKey, NSURLIsRegularFileKey];
402 NSDirectoryEnumerator *enumerator = [fileManager enumeratorAtURL:baseURL includingPropertiesForKeys:
403 propertyKeys options:NSDirectoryEnumerationSkipsSubdirectoryDescendants
404 errorHandler:nil];
405
406 RetainPtr<NSMutableArray> urlsToDelete = adoptNS([[NSMutableArray alloc] init]);
407 for (NSURL *fileURL : enumerator) {
408 NSDictionary *fileAttributes = [fileURL resourceValuesForKeys:propertyKeys error:nil];
409
410 if (![fileAttributes[NSURLNameKey] hasPrefix:@"CachedMedia-"])
411 continue;
412
413 if (![fileAttributes[NSURLIsRegularFileKey] boolValue])
414 continue;
415
416 if (toSystemClockTime(fileAttributes[NSURLContentModificationDateKey]) <= modifiedSince)
417 continue;
418
419 [urlsToDelete addObject:fileURL];
420 }
421
422 for (NSURL *fileURL in urlsToDelete.get())
423 [fileManager removeItemAtURL:fileURL error:nil];
424}
425
426void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::clearMediaCacheForOrigins(const String& path, const HashSet<SecurityOriginData>& origins)
427{
428 AVAssetCache* assetCache = assetCacheForPath(path);
429 if (!assetCache)
430 return;
431
432 for (NSString *key in [assetCache allKeys]) {
433 URL keyAsURL = URL(URL(), key);
434 if (keyAsURL.isValid()) {
435 if (origins.contains(SecurityOriginData::fromURL(keyAsURL)))
436 [assetCache removeEntryForKey:key];
437 }
438 }
439}

451MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::~MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC()
452{
453 weakPtrFactory().revokeAll();
454
455 [[m_avAsset.get() resourceLoader] setDelegate:nil queue:0];
456
457 for (auto& pair : m_resourceLoaderMap)
458 pair.value->invalidate();
459
460 [m_videoOutput setDelegate:nil queue:0];
461
462 if (m_videoLayer)
463 destroyVideoLayer();
464
465 cancelLoad();
466}

468void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::cancelLoad()
469{
470 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
471 tearDownVideoRendering();
472
473 [[NSNotificationCenter defaultCenter] removeObserver:m_objcObserver.get()];
474 [m_objcObserver.get() disconnect];
475
476 // Tell our observer to do nothing when our cancellation of pending loading calls its completion handler.
477 setIgnoreLoadStateChanges(true);
478 if (m_avAsset) {
479 [m_avAsset.get() cancelLoading];
480 m_avAsset = nil;
481 }
482
483 clearTextTracks();
484
485 if (m_legibleOutput) {
486 if (m_avPlayerItem)
487 [m_avPlayerItem.get() removeOutput:m_legibleOutput.get()];
488 m_legibleOutput = nil;
489 }
490
491 if (m_metadataCollector) {
492 // FIXME - removeMediaDataCollector sometimes crashes, do not uncomment this until rdar://56617504 has been fixed.
493 // if (m_avPlayerItem)
494 // [m_avPlayerItem.get() removeMediaDataCollector:m_metadataCollector.get()];
495 m_metadataCollector = nil;
496 }
497
498 if (m_metadataOutput) {
499 if (m_avPlayerItem)
500 [m_avPlayerItem.get() removeOutput:m_metadataOutput.get()];
501 m_metadataOutput = nil;
502 }
503
504 if (m_avPlayerItem) {
505 for (NSString *keyName in itemKVOProperties())
506 [m_avPlayerItem.get() removeObserver:m_objcObserver.get() forKeyPath:keyName];
507
508 m_avPlayerItem = nil;
509 }
510 if (m_avPlayer) {
511 if (m_timeObserver)
512 [m_avPlayer.get() removeTimeObserver:m_timeObserver.get()];
513 m_timeObserver = nil;
514
515 for (NSString *keyName in playerKVOProperties())
516 [m_avPlayer.get() removeObserver:m_objcObserver.get() forKeyPath:keyName];
517
518 setShouldObserveTimeControlStatus(false);
519
520 [m_avPlayer replaceCurrentItemWithPlayerItem:nil];
521#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
522 [m_avPlayer setOutputContext:nil];
523#endif
524
525 if (m_currentTimeObserver)
526 [m_avPlayer removeTimeObserver:m_currentTimeObserver.get()];
527 m_currentTimeObserver = nil;
528
529 m_avPlayer = nil;
530 }
531
532 // Reset cached properties
533 m_createAssetPending = false;
534 m_haveCheckedPlayability = false;
535 m_pendingStatusChanges = 0;
536 m_cachedItemStatus = MediaPlayerAVPlayerItemStatusDoesNotExist;
537 m_cachedSeekableRanges = nullptr;
538 m_cachedLoadedRanges = nullptr;
539 m_cachedHasEnabledAudio = false;
540 m_cachedPresentationSize = FloatSize();
541 m_cachedDuration = MediaTime::zeroTime();
542
543 for (AVPlayerItemTrack *track in m_cachedTracks.get())
544 [track removeObserver:m_objcObserver.get() forKeyPath:@"enabled"];
545 m_cachedTracks = nullptr;
546
547#if ENABLE(WEB_AUDIO) && USE(MEDIATOOLBOX)
548 if (m_provider) {
549 m_provider->setPlayerItem(nullptr);
550 m_provider->setAudioTrack(nullptr);
551 }
552#endif
553
554 setIgnoreLoadStateChanges(false);
555}

603void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::createVideoLayer()
604{
605 if (!m_avPlayer || m_haveBeenAskedToCreateLayer)
606 return;
607
608 callOnMainThread([this, weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this)] {
609 if (!weakThis)
610 return;
611
612 if (!m_avPlayer || m_haveBeenAskedToCreateLayer)
613 return;
614 m_haveBeenAskedToCreateLayer = true;
615
616 if (!m_videoLayer)
617 createAVPlayerLayer();
618
619 if (!m_videoOutput)
620 createVideoOutput();
621
622 player()->renderingModeChanged();
623 });
624}
625
626void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::createAVPlayerLayer()
627{
628 if (!m_avPlayer)
629 return;
630
631 m_videoLayer = adoptNS([PAL::allocAVPlayerLayerInstance() init]);
632 [m_videoLayer setPlayer:m_avPlayer.get()];
633
634 [m_videoLayer setName:@"MediaPlayerPrivate AVPlayerLayer"];
635 [m_videoLayer addObserver:m_objcObserver.get() forKeyPath:@"readyForDisplay" options:NSKeyValueObservingOptionNew context:(void *)MediaPlayerAVFoundationObservationContextAVPlayerLayer];
636 updateVideoLayerGravity();
637 [m_videoLayer setContentsScale:player()->playerContentsScale()];
638 IntSize defaultSize = snappedIntRect(player()->playerContentBoxRect()).size();
639 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
640
641 m_videoLayerManager->setVideoLayer(m_videoLayer.get(), defaultSize);
642
643#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY) && !PLATFORM(WATCHOS) && !PLATFORM(APPLETV)
644 if ([m_videoLayer respondsToSelector:@selector(setPIPModeEnabled:)])
645 [m_videoLayer setPIPModeEnabled:(player()->fullscreenMode() & MediaPlayer::VideoFullscreenModePictureInPicture)];
646#endif
647}
648
649void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::destroyVideoLayer()
650{
651 if (!m_videoLayer)
652 return;
653
654 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
655
656 [m_videoLayer removeObserver:m_objcObserver.get() forKeyPath:@"readyForDisplay"];
657 [m_videoLayer setPlayer:nil];
658 m_videoLayerManager->didDestroyVideoLayer();
659
660 m_videoLayer = nil;
661}

663MediaTime MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::getStartDate() const
664{
665 // Date changes as the track's playback position changes. Must subtract currentTime (offset in seconds) from date offset to get date beginning
666 double date = [[m_avPlayerItem currentDate] timeIntervalSince1970] * 1000;
667
668 // No live streams were made during the epoch (1970). AVFoundation returns 0 if the media file doesn't have a start date
669 if (!date)
670 return MediaTime::invalidTime();
671
672 double currentTime = PAL::CMTimeGetSeconds([m_avPlayerItem currentTime]) * 1000;
673
674 // Rounding due to second offset error when subtracting.
675 return MediaTime::createWithDouble(round(date - currentTime));
676}

718void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::synchronizeTextTrackState()
719{
720 const auto& outOfBandTrackSources = player()->outOfBandTrackSources();
721
722 for (auto& textTrack : m_textTracks) {
723 if (textTrack->textTrackCategory() != InbandTextTrackPrivateAVF::OutOfBand)
724 continue;
725
726 RefPtr<OutOfBandTextTrackPrivateAVF> trackPrivate = static_cast<OutOfBandTextTrackPrivateAVF*>(textTrack.get());
727 RetainPtr<AVMediaSelectionOption> currentOption = trackPrivate->mediaSelectionOption();
728
729 for (auto& track : outOfBandTrackSources) {
730 RetainPtr<CFStringRef> uniqueID = String::number(track->uniqueId()).createCFString();
731
732 if (![[currentOption.get() outOfBandIdentifier] isEqual:(__bridge NSString *)uniqueID.get()])
733 continue;
734
735 InbandTextTrackPrivate::Mode mode = InbandTextTrackPrivate::Mode::Hidden;
736 switch (track->mode()) {
737 case PlatformTextTrackData::TrackMode::Hidden:
738 mode = InbandTextTrackPrivate::Mode::Hidden;
739 break;
740 case PlatformTextTrackData::TrackMode::Disabled:
741 mode = InbandTextTrackPrivate::Mode::Disabled;
742 break;
743 case PlatformTextTrackData::TrackMode::Showing:
744 mode = InbandTextTrackPrivate::Mode::Showing;
745 break;
746 }
747
748 textTrack->setMode(mode);
749 break;
750 }
751 }
752}

811
812static URL conformFragmentIdentifierForURL(const URL& url)
813{
814#if PLATFORM(MAC)
815 // On some versions of macOS, Photos.framework has overriden utility methods from AVFoundation that cause
816 // a exception to be thrown when parsing fragment identifiers from a URL. Their implementation requires
817 // an even number of components when splitting the fragment identifier with separator characters ['&','='].
818 // Work around this broken implementation by pre-parsing the fragment and ensuring that it meets their
819 // criteria. Problematic strings from the TC0051.html test include "t=3&", and this problem generally is
820 // with subtrings between the '&' character not including an equal sign.
821 auto hasInvalidNumberOfEqualCharacters = [](const StringView& fragmentParameter) {
822 auto results = fragmentParameter.splitAllowingEmptyEntries('=');
823 auto iterator = results.begin();
824 return iterator == results.end() || ++iterator == results.end() || ++iterator != results.end();
825 };
826
827 StringBuilder replacementFragmentIdentifierBuilder;
828 bool firstParameter = true;
829 bool hasInvalidFragmentIdentifier = false;
830
831 for (auto fragmentParameter : url.fragmentIdentifier().splitAllowingEmptyEntries('&')) {
832 if (hasInvalidNumberOfEqualCharacters(fragmentParameter)) {
833 hasInvalidFragmentIdentifier = true;
834 continue;
835 }
836 if (!firstParameter)
837 replacementFragmentIdentifierBuilder.append('&');
838 else
839 firstParameter = false;
840 replacementFragmentIdentifierBuilder.append(fragmentParameter);
841 }
842
843 if (!hasInvalidFragmentIdentifier)
844 return url;
845
846 URL validURL = url;
847 if (replacementFragmentIdentifierBuilder.isEmpty())
848 validURL.removeFragmentIdentifier();
849 else
850 validURL.setFragmentIdentifier(replacementFragmentIdentifierBuilder.toString());
851
852 return validURL;
853#else
854 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
855 return url;
856#endif
857}

859void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::createAVAssetForURL(const URL& url, RetainPtr<NSMutableDictionary> options)
860{
861 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
862
863 m_createAssetPending = false;
864
865 if (m_avAsset)
866 return;
867
868 setDelayCallbacks(true);
869
870 [options.get() setObject:@(AVAssetReferenceRestrictionForbidRemoteReferenceToLocal | AVAssetReferenceRestrictionForbidLocalReferenceToRemote) forKey:AVURLAssetReferenceRestrictionsKey];
871
872 RetainPtr<NSMutableDictionary> headerFields = adoptNS([[NSMutableDictionary alloc] init]);
873
874 String referrer = player()->referrer();
875 if (!referrer.isEmpty())
876 [headerFields.get() setObject:referrer forKey:@"Referer"];
877
878 String userAgent = player()->userAgent();
879 if (!userAgent.isEmpty())
880 [headerFields.get() setObject:userAgent forKey:@"User-Agent"];
881
882 if ([headerFields.get() count])
883 [options.get() setObject:headerFields.get() forKey:@"AVURLAssetHTTPHeaderFieldsKey"];
884
885 if (player()->doesHaveAttribute("x-itunes-inherit-uri-query-component"))
886 [options.get() setObject:@YES forKey: AVURLAssetInheritURIQueryComponentFromReferencingURIKey];
887
888 if (PAL::canLoad_AVFoundation_AVURLAssetUseClientURLLoadingExclusively())
889 [options setObject:@YES forKey:AVURLAssetUseClientURLLoadingExclusively];
890#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
891 else if (PAL::canLoad_AVFoundation_AVURLAssetRequiresCustomURLLoadingKey())
892 [options setObject:@YES forKey:AVURLAssetRequiresCustomURLLoadingKey];
893 // FIXME: rdar://problem/20354688
894 String identifier = player()->sourceApplicationIdentifier();
895 if (!identifier.isEmpty())
896 [options setObject:identifier forKey:AVURLAssetClientBundleIdentifierKey];
897#endif
898
899 auto type = player()->contentMIMEType();
900
901 // Don't advertise WebM MIME types or the format reader won't be loaded until rdar://72405127 is fixed.
902 auto willUseWebMFormatReader = willUseWebMFormatReaderForType(type);
903
904 if (PAL::canLoad_AVFoundation_AVURLAssetOutOfBandMIMETypeKey() && !type.isEmpty() && !player()->contentMIMETypeWasInferredFromExtension() && !willUseWebMFormatReader) {
905 auto codecs = player()->contentTypeCodecs();
906 if (!codecs.isEmpty()) {
907 NSString *typeString = [NSString stringWithFormat:@"%@; codecs=\"%@\"", (NSString *)type, (NSString *)codecs];
908 [options setObject:typeString forKey:AVURLAssetOutOfBandMIMETypeKey];
909 } else
910 [options setObject:(NSString *)type forKey:AVURLAssetOutOfBandMIMETypeKey];
911 }
912
913#if ENABLE(AVF_CAPTIONS)
914 auto outOfBandTrackSources = player()->outOfBandTrackSources();
915 if (!outOfBandTrackSources.isEmpty()) {
916 auto outOfBandTracks = createNSArray(outOfBandTrackSources, [] (auto& trackSource) {
917 return @{
918 AVOutOfBandAlternateTrackDisplayNameKey: trackSource->label(),
919 AVOutOfBandAlternateTrackExtendedLanguageTagKey: trackSource->language(),
920 AVOutOfBandAlternateTrackIsDefaultKey: trackSource->isDefault() ? @YES : @NO,
921 AVOutOfBandAlternateTrackIdentifierKey: String::number(trackSource->uniqueId()),
922 AVOutOfBandAlternateTrackSourceKey: trackSource->url(),
923 AVOutOfBandAlternateTrackMediaCharactersticsKey: mediaDescriptionForKind(trackSource->kind()),
924 };
925 });
926
927 [options.get() setObject:outOfBandTracks.get() forKey:AVURLAssetOutOfBandAlternateTracksKey];
928 }
929#endif
930
931#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
932 String networkInterfaceName = player()->mediaPlayerNetworkInterfaceName();
933 if (!networkInterfaceName.isEmpty())
934 [options setObject:networkInterfaceName forKey:AVURLAssetBoundNetworkInterfaceName];
935#endif
936
937 bool usePersistentCache = player()->shouldUsePersistentCache();
938 [options setObject:@(!usePersistentCache) forKey:AVURLAssetUsesNoPersistentCacheKey];
939
940 if (usePersistentCache) {
941 if (auto* assetCache = ensureAssetCacheExistsForPath(player()->mediaCacheDirectory()))
942 [options setObject:assetCache forKey:AVURLAssetCacheKey];
943 else
944 [options setObject:@NO forKey:AVURLAssetUsesNoPersistentCacheKey];
945 }
946
947 if (willUseWebMFormatReader)
948 registerFormatReaderIfNecessary();
949
950 NSURL *cocoaURL = canonicalURL(url);
951
952 @try {
953 m_avAsset = adoptNS([PAL::allocAVURLAssetInstance() initWithURL:cocoaURL options:options.get()]);
954 } @catch(NSException *exception) {
955 ERROR_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "-[AVURLAssetInstance initWithURL:cocoaURL options:] threw an exception: ", [[exception name] UTF8String], ", reason : ", [[exception reason] UTF8String]);
956 cocoaURL = canonicalURL(conformFragmentIdentifierForURL(url));
957
958 @try {
959 m_avAsset = adoptNS([PAL::allocAVURLAssetInstance() initWithURL:cocoaURL options:options.get()]);
960 } @catch(NSException *exception) {
961 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
962 ERROR_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "-[AVURLAssetInstance initWithURL:cocoaURL options:] threw a second exception, bailing: ", [[exception name] UTF8String], ", reason : ", [[exception reason] UTF8String]);
963 setNetworkState(MediaPlayer::NetworkState::FormatError);
964 return;
965 }
966 }
967
968 AVAssetResourceLoader *resourceLoader = m_avAsset.get().resourceLoader;
969 [resourceLoader setDelegate:m_loaderDelegate.get() queue:globalLoaderDelegateQueue()];
970
971 if (DeprecatedGlobalSettings::isAVFoundationNSURLSessionEnabled()
972 && [resourceLoader respondsToSelector:@selector(setURLSession:)]
973 && [resourceLoader respondsToSelector:@selector(URLSessionDataDelegate)]
974 && [resourceLoader respondsToSelector:@selector(URLSessionDataDelegateQueue)]) {
975 RefPtr<PlatformMediaResourceLoader> mediaResourceLoader = player()->createResourceLoader();
976 if (mediaResourceLoader)
977 resourceLoader.URLSession = (NSURLSession *)adoptNS([[WebCoreNSURLSession alloc] initWithResourceLoader:*mediaResourceLoader delegate:resourceLoader.URLSessionDataDelegate delegateQueue:resourceLoader.URLSessionDataDelegateQueue]).get();
978 }
979
980 m_haveCheckedPlayability = false;
981
982 setDelayCallbacks(false);
983
984 checkPlayability();
985}

1095 setDelayCallbacks(false);

1098static NSString* audioTimePitchAlgorithmForMediaPlayerPitchCorrectionAlgorithm(MediaPlayer::PitchCorrectionAlgorithm pitchCorrectionAlgorithm, bool preservesPitch, double rate)
1099{

1191void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::beginLoadingMetadata()
1192{
1193 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
1194
1195 OSObjectPtr<dispatch_group_t> metadataLoadingGroup = adoptOSObject(dispatch_group_create());
1196 dispatch_group_enter(metadataLoadingGroup.get());
1197 auto weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this);
1198 [m_avAsset.get() loadValuesAsynchronouslyForKeys:assetMetadataKeyNames() completionHandler:^{
1199 callOnMainThread([weakThis, metadataLoadingGroup] {
1200 if (weakThis && [weakThis->m_avAsset.get() statusOfValueForKey:@"tracks" error:nil] == AVKeyValueStatusLoaded) {
1201 for (AVAssetTrack *track in [weakThis->m_avAsset.get() tracks]) {
1202 dispatch_group_enter(metadataLoadingGroup.get());
1203 [track loadValuesAsynchronouslyForKeys:assetTrackMetadataKeyNames() completionHandler:^{
1204 dispatch_group_leave(metadataLoadingGroup.get());
1205 }];
1206 }
1207 }
1208 dispatch_group_leave(metadataLoadingGroup.get());
1209 });
1210 }];
1211
1212 dispatch_group_notify(metadataLoadingGroup.get(), dispatch_get_main_queue(), ^{
1213 callOnMainThread([weakThis] {
1214 if (weakThis)
1215 [weakThis->m_objcObserver.get() metadataLoaded];
1216 });
1217 });
1218}

1280 videoGravity = AVLayerVideoGravityResize;
1281 else if (gravity == MediaPlayer::VideoGravity::ResizeAspect)
1282 videoGravity = AVLayerVideoGravityResizeAspect;
1283 else if (gravity == MediaPlayer::VideoGravity::ResizeAspectFill)
1284 videoGravity = AVLayerVideoGravityResizeAspectFill;
1285 else
1286 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1287
1288 if ([m_videoLayer videoGravity] == videoGravity)
1289 return;
1290
1291 [m_videoLayer setVideoGravity:videoGravity];
1292 syncTextTrackBounds();
1293}

1388MediaTime MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::platformDuration() const
1389{
1390 // Do not ask the asset for duration before it has been loaded or it will fetch the
1391 // answer synchronously.
1392 if (!m_avAsset || assetStatus() < MediaPlayerAVAssetStatusLoaded)
1393 return MediaTime::invalidTime();
1394
1395 CMTime cmDuration;
1396
1397 // Check the AVItem if we have one and it has loaded duration, some assets never report duration.
1398 if (m_avPlayerItem && playerItemStatus() >= MediaPlayerAVPlayerItemStatusReadyToPlay)
1399 cmDuration = [m_avPlayerItem.get() duration];
1400 else
1401 cmDuration = [m_avAsset.get() duration];
1402
1403 if (CMTIME_IS_NUMERIC(cmDuration))
1404 return PAL::toMediaTime(cmDuration);
1405
1406 if (CMTIME_IS_INDEFINITE(cmDuration))
1407 return MediaTime::positiveInfiniteTime();
1408
1409 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "returning invalid time");
1410 return MediaTime::invalidTime();
1411}

1418MediaTime MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::currentMediaTime() const
1419{
1420 if (!metaDataAvailable() || !m_avPlayerItem)
1421 return MediaTime::zeroTime();
1422
1423 if (!m_wallClockAtCachedCurrentTime)
1424 currentMediaTimeDidChange(PAL::toMediaTime([m_avPlayerItem.get() currentTime]));
1425 ASSERT(m_wallClockAtCachedCurrentTime);
1426
1427 auto itemTime = m_cachedCurrentMediaTime;
1428 if (!itemTime.isFinite())
1429 return MediaTime::zeroTime();
1430
1431 if (m_timeControlStatusAtCachedCurrentTime == AVPlayerTimeControlStatusPlaying) {
1432 auto elapsedMediaTime = (WallTime::now() - *m_wallClockAtCachedCurrentTime) * m_requestedRateAtCachedCurrentTime;
1433 itemTime += MediaTime::createWithDouble(elapsedMediaTime.seconds());
1434 }
1435
1436 return std::min(std::max(itemTime, MediaTime::zeroTime()), m_cachedDuration);
1437}

1456void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::seekToTime(const MediaTime& time, const MediaTime& negativeTolerance, const MediaTime& positiveTolerance)
1457{
1458 // setCurrentTime generates several event callbacks, update afterwards.
1459 setDelayCallbacks(true);
1460
1461 if (m_metadataTrack)
1462 m_metadataTrack->flushPartialCues();
1463
1464 CMTime cmTime = PAL::toCMTime(time);
1465 CMTime cmBefore = PAL::toCMTime(negativeTolerance);
1466 CMTime cmAfter = PAL::toCMTime(positiveTolerance);
1467
1468 // [AVPlayerItem seekToTime] will throw an exception if toleranceBefore is negative.
1469 if (PAL::CMTimeCompare(cmBefore, PAL::kCMTimeZero) < 0)
1470 cmBefore = PAL::kCMTimeZero;
1471
1472 auto weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this);
1473
1474 setShouldObserveTimeControlStatus(false);
1475 [m_avPlayerItem.get() seekToTime:cmTime toleranceBefore:cmBefore toleranceAfter:cmAfter completionHandler:^(BOOL finished) {
1476 callOnMainThread([weakThis, finished] {
1477 auto _this = weakThis.get();
1478 if (!_this)
1479 return;
1480
1481 _this->setShouldObserveTimeControlStatus(true);
1482 _this->seekCompleted(finished);
1483 });
1484 }];
1485
1486 setDelayCallbacks(false);
1487}

1588

1602MediaTime MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::platformMinTimeSeekable() const
1603{
1604 using namespace PAL; // For CMTIMERANGE_IS_EMPTY.
1605
1606 if (!m_cachedSeekableRanges || ![m_cachedSeekableRanges count])
1607 return MediaTime::zeroTime();
1608
1609 MediaTime minTimeSeekable = MediaTime::positiveInfiniteTime();
1610 bool hasValidRange = false;
1611 for (NSValue *thisRangeValue in m_cachedSeekableRanges.get()) {
1612 CMTimeRange timeRange = [thisRangeValue CMTimeRangeValue];
1613 if (!CMTIMERANGE_IS_VALID(timeRange) || CMTIMERANGE_IS_EMPTY(timeRange))
1614 continue;
1615
1616 hasValidRange = true;
1617 MediaTime startOfRange = PAL::toMediaTime(timeRange.start);
1618 if (minTimeSeekable > startOfRange)
1619 minTimeSeekable = startOfRange;
1620 }
1621 return hasValidRange ? minTimeSeekable : MediaTime::zeroTime();
1622}

1687MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundation::AssetStatus MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::assetStatus() const
1688{
1689 if (!m_avAsset)
1690 return MediaPlayerAVAssetStatusDoesNotExist;
1691
1692 if (!m_cachedAssetIsLoaded) {
1693 for (NSString *keyName in assetMetadataKeyNames()) {
1694 NSError *error = nil;
1695 AVKeyValueStatus keyStatus = [m_avAsset.get() statusOfValueForKey:keyName error:&error];
1696
1697 if (error)
1698 ERROR_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "failed for ", [keyName UTF8String], ", error = ", [[error localizedDescription] UTF8String]);
1699
1700 if (keyStatus < AVKeyValueStatusLoaded)
1701 return MediaPlayerAVAssetStatusLoading; // At least one key is not loaded yet.
1702
1703 if (keyStatus == AVKeyValueStatusFailed)
1704 return MediaPlayerAVAssetStatusFailed; // At least one key could not be loaded.
1705
1706 if (keyStatus == AVKeyValueStatusCancelled)
1707 return MediaPlayerAVAssetStatusCancelled; // Loading of at least one key was cancelled.
1708 }
1709 m_cachedAssetIsLoaded = true;
1710 }
1711
1712 if (!player()->shouldCheckHardwareSupport())
1713 m_tracksArePlayable = true;
1714
1715 if (!m_tracksArePlayable) {
1716 m_tracksArePlayable = true;
1717 for (AVAssetTrack *track in [m_avAsset tracks]) {
1718 if (!assetTrackMeetsHardwareDecodeRequirements(track, player()->mediaContentTypesRequiringHardwareSupport())) {
1719 m_tracksArePlayable = false;
1720 break;
1721 }
1722 }
1723 }
1724
1725 if (!m_cachedAssetIsPlayable)
1726 m_cachedAssetIsPlayable = [[m_avAsset.get() valueForKey:@"playable"] boolValue];
1727
1728 if (*m_cachedAssetIsPlayable && m_tracksArePlayable.value())
1729 return MediaPlayerAVAssetStatusPlayable;
1730
1731 return MediaPlayerAVAssetStatusLoaded;
1732}

1734long MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::assetErrorCode() const
1735{
1736 if (!m_avAsset)
1737 return 0;
1738
1739 NSError *error = nil;
1740 [m_avAsset statusOfValueForKey:@"playable" error:&error];
1741 return [error code];
1742}
1743
1744void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::paintCurrentFrameInContext(GraphicsContext& context, const FloatRect& rect)
1745{
1746 if (!metaDataAvailable() || context.paintingDisabled() || isCurrentPlaybackTargetWireless())
1747 return;
1748
1749 setDelayCallbacks(true);
1750 BEGIN_BLOCK_OBJC_EXCEPTIONS
1751
1752 // Callers of this will often call copyVideoTextureToPlatformTexture first,
1753 // which calls updateLastPixelBuffer, which clears m_lastImage whenever the
1754 // video delivers a new frame. This breaks videoOutputHasAvailableFrame's
1755 // short-circuiting when m_lastImage is non-null, but the video often
1756 // doesn't have a new frame to deliver since the last time
1757 // hasNewPixelBufferForItemTime was called against m_videoOutput. To avoid
1758 // changing the semantics of videoOutputHasAvailableFrame in ways that might
1759 // break other callers, look for production of a recent pixel buffer from
1760 // the video output, too.
1761 if (videoOutputHasAvailableFrame() || (m_videoOutput && m_lastPixelBuffer))
1762 paintWithVideoOutput(context, rect);
1763 else
1764 paintWithImageGenerator(context, rect);
1765
1766 END_BLOCK_OBJC_EXCEPTIONS
1767 setDelayCallbacks(false);
1768
1769 m_videoFrameHasDrawn = true;
1770}
1771
1772void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::paint(GraphicsContext& context, const FloatRect& rect)
1773{
1774 if (!metaDataAvailable() || context.paintingDisabled())
1775 return;
1776
1777 // We can ignore the request if we are already rendering to a layer.
1778 if (currentRenderingMode() == MediaRenderingToLayer)
1779 return;
1780
1781 // paint() is best effort, so only paint if we already have an image generator or video output available.
1782 if (!hasContextRenderer())
1783 return;
1784
1785 paintCurrentFrameInContext(context, rect);
1786}
1787
1788void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::paintWithImageGenerator(GraphicsContext& context, const FloatRect& rect)
1789{
1790 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
1791
1792 RetainPtr<CGImageRef> image = createImageForTimeInRect(currentTime(), rect);
1793 if (image) {
1794 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(context);
1795 context.translate(rect.x(), rect.y() + rect.height());
1796 context.scale(FloatSize(1.0f, -1.0f));
1797 context.setImageInterpolationQuality(InterpolationQuality::Low);
1798 IntRect paintRect(IntPoint(0, 0), IntSize(rect.width(), rect.height()));
1799 CGContextDrawImage(context.platformContext(), CGRectMake(0, 0, paintRect.width(), paintRect.height()), image.get());
1800 }
1801}
1802
1803RetainPtr<CGImageRef> MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::createImageForTimeInRect(float time, const FloatRect& rect)
1804{
1805 if (!m_imageGenerator)
1806 createImageGenerator();
1807 ASSERT(m_imageGenerator);
1808
1809 MonotonicTime start = MonotonicTime::now();
1810
1811 [m_imageGenerator.get() setMaximumSize:CGSize(rect.size())];
1812 RetainPtr<CGImageRef> rawImage = adoptCF([m_imageGenerator.get() copyCGImageAtTime:PAL::CMTimeMakeWithSeconds(time, 600) actualTime:nil error:nil]);
1813 RetainPtr<CGImageRef> image = adoptCF(CGImageCreateCopyWithColorSpace(rawImage.get(), sRGBColorSpaceRef()));
1814
1815 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "creating image took ", (MonotonicTime::now() - start).seconds());
1816
1817 return image;
1818}

1878#if ENABLE(LEGACY_ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
1879static void fulfillRequestWithKeyData(AVAssetResourceLoadingRequest *request, ArrayBuffer* keyData)
1880{
1881 if (AVAssetResourceLoadingContentInformationRequest *infoRequest = [request contentInformationRequest]) {
1882 [infoRequest setContentLength:keyData->byteLength()];
1883 [infoRequest setByteRangeAccessSupported:YES];
1884 }
1885
1886 if (AVAssetResourceLoadingDataRequest *dataRequest = [request dataRequest]) {
1887 long long start = [dataRequest currentOffset];
1888 long long end = std::min<long long>(keyData->byteLength(), [dataRequest currentOffset] + [dataRequest requestedLength]);
1889
1890 if (start < 0 || end < 0 || start >= static_cast<long long>(keyData->byteLength())) {
1891 [request finishLoadingWithError:nil];
1892 return;
1893 }
1894
1895 ASSERT(start <= std::numeric_limits<int>::max());
1896 ASSERT(end <= std::numeric_limits<int>::max());
1897 auto requestedKeyData = keyData->slice(static_cast<int>(start), static_cast<int>(end));
1898 RetainPtr<NSData> nsData = adoptNS([[NSData alloc] initWithBytes:requestedKeyData->data() length:requestedKeyData->byteLength()]);
1899 [dataRequest respondWithData:nsData.get()];
1900 }
1901
1902 [request finishLoading];
1903}
1904#endif
1905
1906bool MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::shouldWaitForLoadingOfResource(AVAssetResourceLoadingRequest* avRequest)
1907{
1908 String scheme = [[[avRequest request] URL] scheme];
1909 String keyURI = [[[avRequest request] URL] absoluteString];
1910
1911#if ENABLE(LEGACY_ENCRYPTED_MEDIA) || ENABLE(ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
1912 if (scheme == "skd") {
1913#if ENABLE(LEGACY_ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
1914 // Create an initData with the following layout:
1915 // [4 bytes: keyURI size], [keyURI size bytes: keyURI]
1916 unsigned keyURISize = keyURI.length() * sizeof(UChar);
1917 auto initDataBuffer = ArrayBuffer::create(4 + keyURISize, 1);
1918 unsigned byteLength = initDataBuffer->byteLength();
1919 auto initDataView = JSC::DataView::create(initDataBuffer.copyRef(), 0, byteLength);
1920 initDataView->set<uint32_t>(0, keyURISize, true);
1921
1922 auto keyURIArray = Uint16Array::create(initDataBuffer.copyRef(), 4, keyURI.length());
1923 keyURIArray->setRange(reinterpret_cast<const UniChar*>(StringView(keyURI).upconvertedCharacters().get()), keyURI.length() / sizeof(unsigned char), 0);
1924
1925 auto initData = Uint8Array::create(WTFMove(initDataBuffer), 0, byteLength);
1926 player()->keyNeeded(initData.ptr());
1927#if ENABLE(ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
1928 if (!player()->shouldContinueAfterKeyNeeded())
1929 return true;
1930#endif
1931#endif
1932
1933#if ENABLE(ENCRYPTED_MEDIA) && HAVE(AVCONTENTKEYSESSION)
1934 if (m_cdmInstance) {
1935 avRequest.contentInformationRequest.contentType = AVStreamingKeyDeliveryContentKeyType;
1936 [avRequest finishLoading];
1937 return true;
1938 }
1939
1940 RetainPtr<NSData> keyURIData = [keyURI dataUsingEncoding:NSUTF8StringEncoding allowLossyConversion:YES];
1941 m_keyID = SharedBuffer::create(keyURIData.get());
1942 player()->initializationDataEncountered("skd"_s, m_keyID->tryCreateArrayBuffer());
1943 setWaitingForKey(true);
1944#endif
1945 m_keyURIToRequestMap.set(keyURI, avRequest);
1946
1947 return true;
1948 }
1949
1950#if ENABLE(LEGACY_ENCRYPTED_MEDIA)
1951 if (scheme == "clearkey") {
1952 String keyID = [[[avRequest request] URL] resourceSpecifier];
1953 auto encodedKeyId = UTF8Encoding().encode(keyID, UnencodableHandling::URLEncodedEntities);
1954
1955 auto initData = Uint8Array::create(encodedKeyId.size());
1956 initData->setRange(encodedKeyId.data(), encodedKeyId.size(), 0);
1957
1958 auto keyData = player()->cachedKeyForKeyId(keyID);
1959 if (keyData) {
1960 fulfillRequestWithKeyData(avRequest, keyData.get());
1961 return false;
1962 }
1963
1964 player()->keyNeeded(initData.ptr());
1965
1966 if (!player()->shouldContinueAfterKeyNeeded())
1967 return false;
1968
1969 m_keyURIToRequestMap.set(keyID, avRequest);
1970 return true;
1971 }
1972#endif
1973#endif
1974
1975 auto resourceLoader = WebCoreAVFResourceLoader::create(this, avRequest);
1976 m_resourceLoaderMap.add((__bridge CFTypeRef)avRequest, resourceLoader.copyRef());
1977 resourceLoader->startLoading();
1978 return true;
1979}

2039void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::tracksChanged()
2040{
2041 String primaryAudioTrackLanguage = m_languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack;
2042 m_languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack = String();
2043
2044 if (!m_avAsset)
2045 return;
2046
2047 setDelayCharacteristicsChangedNotification(true);
2048
2049 bool haveCCTrack = false;
2050 bool hasCaptions = false;
2051
2052 // This is called whenever the tracks collection changes so cache hasVideo and hasAudio since we are
2053 // asked about those fairly fequently.
2054 if (!m_avPlayerItem) {
2055 // We don't have a player item yet, so check with the asset because some assets support inspection
2056 // prior to becoming ready to play.
2057 AVAssetTrack* firstEnabledVideoTrack = firstEnabledTrack([m_avAsset.get() tracksWithMediaCharacteristic:AVMediaCharacteristicVisual]);
2058 setHasVideo(firstEnabledVideoTrack);
2059 setHasAudio(firstEnabledTrack([m_avAsset.get() tracksWithMediaCharacteristic:AVMediaCharacteristicAudible]));
2060 auto size = firstEnabledVideoTrack ? FloatSize(CGSizeApplyAffineTransform([firstEnabledVideoTrack naturalSize], [firstEnabledVideoTrack preferredTransform])) : FloatSize();
2061 // For videos with rotation tag set, the transformation above might return a CGSize instance with negative width or height.
2062 // See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=172648.
2063 if (size.width() < 0)
2064 size.setWidth(-size.width());
2065 if (size.height() < 0)
2066 size.setHeight(-size.height());
2067 presentationSizeDidChange(size);
2068 } else {
2069 bool hasVideo = false;
2070 bool hasAudio = false;
2071 bool hasMetaData = false;
2072 for (AVPlayerItemTrack *track in m_cachedTracks.get()) {
2073 if ([track isEnabled]) {
2074 AVAssetTrack *assetTrack = [track assetTrack];
2075 NSString *mediaType = [assetTrack mediaType];
2076 if ([mediaType isEqualToString:AVMediaTypeVideo])
2077 hasVideo = true;
2078 else if ([mediaType isEqualToString:AVMediaTypeAudio])
2079 hasAudio = true;
2080 else if ([mediaType isEqualToString:AVMediaTypeClosedCaption]) {
2081 haveCCTrack = true;
2082 } else if ([mediaType isEqualToString:AVMediaTypeMetadata]) {
2083 hasMetaData = true;
2084 }
2085 }
2086 }
2087
2088 updateAudioTracks();
2089 updateVideoTracks();
2090
2091 hasAudio |= (m_audibleGroup && m_audibleGroup->selectedOption());
2092 hasVideo |= (m_visualGroup && m_visualGroup->selectedOption());
2093
2094 // HLS streams will occasionally recreate all their tracks; during seek and after
2095 // buffering policy changes. "debounce" notifications which result in no enabled
2096 // audio tracks by also taking AVPlayerItem.hasEnabledAudio into account when determining
2097 // whethere there is any audio present.
2098 hasAudio |= m_cachedHasEnabledAudio;
2099
2100 // Always says we have video if the AVPlayerLayer is ready for diaplay to work around
2101 // an AVFoundation bug which causes it to sometimes claim a track is disabled even
2102 // when it is not.
2103 setHasVideo(hasVideo || m_cachedIsReadyForDisplay);
2104
2105 setHasAudio(hasAudio);
2106#if ENABLE(DATACUE_VALUE)
2107 if (hasMetaData)
2108 processMetadataTrack();
2109#endif
2110 }
2111
2112 AVMediaSelectionGroup *legibleGroup = safeMediaSelectionGroupForLegibleMedia();
2113 if (legibleGroup && m_cachedTracks) {
2114 hasCaptions = [[PAL::getAVMediaSelectionGroupClass() playableMediaSelectionOptionsFromArray:[legibleGroup options]] count];
2115 if (hasCaptions)
2116 processMediaSelectionOptions();
2117 }
2118
2119 setHasClosedCaptions(hasCaptions);
2120
2121 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "has video = ", hasVideo(), ", has audio = ", hasAudio(), ", has captions = ", hasClosedCaptions());
2122
2123 sizeChanged();
2124
2125 if (primaryAudioTrackLanguage != languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack())
2126 characteristicsChanged();
2127
2128#if ENABLE(WEB_AUDIO) && USE(MEDIATOOLBOX)
2129 if (m_provider)
2130 m_provider->setAudioTrack(firstEnabledTrack(safeAVAssetTracksForAudibleMedia()));
2131#endif
2132
2133 setDelayCharacteristicsChangedNotification(false);
2134}

2136void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::updateRotationSession()
2137{
2138 AffineTransform finalTransform = m_avAsset.get().preferredTransform;
2139 FloatSize naturalSize;
2140 if (auto* firstEnabledVideoTrack = firstEnabledTrack([m_avAsset.get() tracksWithMediaCharacteristic:AVMediaCharacteristicVisual])) {
2141 naturalSize = FloatSize(firstEnabledVideoTrack.naturalSize);
2142 finalTransform *= firstEnabledVideoTrack.preferredTransform;
2143 }
2144
2145 if (finalTransform.isIdentity()) {
2146 m_imageRotationSession = nullptr;
2147 return;
2148 }
2149
2150 if (m_imageRotationSession
2151 && m_imageRotationSession->transform()
2152 && m_imageRotationSession->transform().value() == finalTransform
2153 && m_imageRotationSession->size() == naturalSize)
2154 return;
2155
2156 m_imageRotationSession = makeUnique<ImageRotationSessionVT>(WTFMove(finalTransform), naturalSize, ImageRotationSessionVT::IsCGImageCompatible::Yes);
2157}

2159template <typename RefT, typename PassRefT>
2160void determineChangedTracksFromNewTracksAndOldItems(NSArray* tracks, NSString* trackType, Vector<RefT>& oldItems, RefT (*itemFactory)(AVPlayerItemTrack*), MediaPlayer* player, void (MediaPlayer::*removedFunction)(PassRefT), void (MediaPlayer::*addedFunction)(PassRefT))
2161{
2162 RetainPtr<NSSet> newTracks = adoptNS([[NSSet alloc] initWithArray:[tracks objectsAtIndexes:[tracks indexesOfObjectsPassingTest:^(id track, NSUInteger, BOOL*){
2163 return [[[track assetTrack] mediaType] isEqualToString:trackType];
2164 }]]]);
2165 RetainPtr<NSMutableSet> oldTracks = adoptNS([[NSMutableSet alloc] initWithCapacity:oldItems.size()]);
2166
2167 for (auto& oldItem : oldItems) {
2168 if (oldItem->playerItemTrack())
2169 [oldTracks addObject:oldItem->playerItemTrack()];
2170 }
2171
2172 // Find the added & removed AVPlayerItemTracks:
2173 RetainPtr<NSMutableSet> removedTracks = adoptNS([oldTracks mutableCopy]);
2174 [removedTracks minusSet:newTracks.get()];
2175
2176 RetainPtr<NSMutableSet> addedTracks = adoptNS([newTracks mutableCopy]);
2177 [addedTracks minusSet:oldTracks.get()];
2178
2179 typedef Vector<RefT> ItemVector;
2180 ItemVector replacementItems;
2181 ItemVector addedItems;
2182 ItemVector removedItems;
2183 for (auto& oldItem : oldItems) {
2184 if (oldItem->playerItemTrack() && [removedTracks containsObject:oldItem->playerItemTrack()])
2185 removedItems.append(oldItem);
2186 else
2187 replacementItems.append(oldItem);
2188 }
2189
2190 for (AVPlayerItemTrack* track in addedTracks.get())
2191 addedItems.append(itemFactory(track));
2192
2193 replacementItems.appendVector(addedItems);
2194 oldItems.swap(replacementItems);
2195
2196 for (auto& removedItem : removedItems)
2197 (player->*removedFunction)(*removedItem);
2198
2199 for (auto& addedItem : addedItems)
2200 (player->*addedFunction)(*addedItem);
2201}
2202
2203template <typename RefT, typename PassRefT>
2204void determineChangedTracksFromNewTracksAndOldItems(MediaSelectionGroupAVFObjC* group, Vector<RefT>& oldItems, const Vector<String>& characteristics, RefT (*itemFactory)(MediaSelectionOptionAVFObjC&), MediaPlayer* player, void (MediaPlayer::*removedFunction)(PassRefT), void (MediaPlayer::*addedFunction)(PassRefT))
2205{
2206 group->updateOptions(characteristics);
2207
2208 ListHashSet<RefPtr<MediaSelectionOptionAVFObjC>> newSelectionOptions;
2209 for (auto& option : group->options()) {
2210 if (!option)
2211 continue;
2212 AVMediaSelectionOption* avOption = option->avMediaSelectionOption();
2213 if (!avOption)
2214 continue;
2215 newSelectionOptions.add(option);
2216 }
2217
2218 ListHashSet<RefPtr<MediaSelectionOptionAVFObjC>> oldSelectionOptions;
2219 for (auto& oldItem : oldItems) {
2220 if (MediaSelectionOptionAVFObjC *option = oldItem->mediaSelectionOption())
2221 oldSelectionOptions.add(option);
2222 }
2223
2224 // Find the added & removed AVMediaSelectionOptions:
2225 ListHashSet<RefPtr<MediaSelectionOptionAVFObjC>> removedSelectionOptions;
2226 for (auto& oldOption : oldSelectionOptions) {
2227 if (!newSelectionOptions.contains(oldOption))
2228 removedSelectionOptions.add(oldOption);
2229 }
2230
2231 ListHashSet<RefPtr<MediaSelectionOptionAVFObjC>> addedSelectionOptions;
2232 for (auto& newOption : newSelectionOptions) {
2233 if (!oldSelectionOptions.contains(newOption))
2234 addedSelectionOptions.add(newOption);
2235 }
2236
2237 typedef Vector<RefT> ItemVector;
2238 ItemVector replacementItems;
2239 ItemVector addedItems;
2240 ItemVector removedItems;
2241 for (auto& oldItem : oldItems) {
2242 if (!oldItem->mediaSelectionOption())
2243 removedItems.append(oldItem);
2244 else if (removedSelectionOptions.contains(oldItem->mediaSelectionOption()))
2245 removedItems.append(oldItem);
2246 else
2247 replacementItems.append(oldItem);
2248 }
2249
2250 for (auto& option : addedSelectionOptions)
2251 addedItems.append(itemFactory(*option.get()));
2252
2253 replacementItems.appendVector(addedItems);
2254 oldItems.swap(replacementItems);
2255
2256 for (auto& removedItem : removedItems)
2257 (player->*removedFunction)(*removedItem);
2258
2259 for (auto& addedItem : addedItems)
2260 (player->*addedFunction)(*addedItem);
2261}

2408bool MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::updateLastPixelBuffer()
2409{
2410 if (!m_avPlayerItem || readyState() < MediaPlayer::ReadyState::HaveCurrentData)
2411 return false;
2412
2413 if (!m_videoOutput)
2414 createVideoOutput();
2415 ASSERT(m_videoOutput);
2416
2417 CMTime currentTime = [m_avPlayerItem.get() currentTime];
2418
2419 if (![m_videoOutput.get() hasNewPixelBufferForItemTime:currentTime])
2420 return false;
2421
2422 m_lastPixelBuffer = adoptCF([m_videoOutput.get() copyPixelBufferForItemTime:currentTime itemTimeForDisplay:nil]);
2423
2424 if (m_imageRotationSession)
2425 m_lastPixelBuffer = m_imageRotationSession->rotate(m_lastPixelBuffer.get());
2426
2427 m_lastImage = nullptr;
2428 return true;

2445void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::updateLastImage(UpdateType type)
2446{
2447 if (!m_avPlayerItem || readyState() < MediaPlayer::ReadyState::HaveCurrentData)
2448 return;
2449
2450 if (type == UpdateType::UpdateSynchronously && !m_lastImage && !videoOutputHasAvailableFrame())
2451 waitForVideoOutputMediaDataWillChange();
2452
2453 // Calls to copyPixelBufferForItemTime:itemTimeForDisplay: may return nil if the pixel buffer
2454 // for the requested time has already been retrieved. In this case, the last valid image (if any)
2455 // should be displayed.
2456 if (!updateLastPixelBuffer() && (m_lastImage || !m_lastPixelBuffer))
2457 return;
2458
2459 if (!m_pixelBufferConformer) {
2460 NSDictionary *attributes = @{ (__bridge NSString *)kCVPixelBufferPixelFormatTypeKey: @(kCVPixelFormatType_32BGRA) };
2461 m_pixelBufferConformer = makeUnique<PixelBufferConformerCV>((__bridge CFDictionaryRef)attributes);
2462 }
2463
2464 MonotonicTime start = MonotonicTime::now();
2465
2466 m_lastImage = NativeImage::create(m_pixelBufferConformer->createImageFromPixelBuffer(m_lastPixelBuffer.get()));
2467
2468 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "creating buffer took ", (MonotonicTime::now() - start).seconds());
2469}

2471void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::paintWithVideoOutput(GraphicsContext& context, const FloatRect& outputRect)
2472{
2473 // It's crucial to not wait synchronously for the next image. Videos that
2474 // come down this path are performing slow-case software uploads, and such
2475 // videos may not return metadata in a timely fashion. Use the most recently
2476 // available pixel buffer, if any.
2477 updateLastImage();
2478 if (!m_lastImage)
2479 return;
2480
2481 AVAssetTrack* firstEnabledVideoTrack = firstEnabledTrack([m_avAsset.get() tracksWithMediaCharacteristic:AVMediaCharacteristicVisual]);
2482 if (!firstEnabledVideoTrack)
2483 return;
2484
2485 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER);
2486
2487 FloatRect imageRect { FloatPoint::zero(), m_lastImage->size() };
2488 context.drawNativeImage(*m_lastImage, imageRect.size(), outputRect, imageRect);
2489
2490 // If we have created an AVAssetImageGenerator in the past due to m_videoOutput not having an available
2491 // video frame, destroy it now that it is no longer needed.
2492 if (m_imageGenerator)
2493 destroyImageGenerator();
2494
2495}

2560void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::outputObscuredDueToInsufficientExternalProtectionChanged(bool newValue)

2683void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::processMediaSelectionOptions()
2684{
2685 AVMediaSelectionGroup *legibleGroup = safeMediaSelectionGroupForLegibleMedia();
2686 if (!legibleGroup) {
2687 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "no mediaSelectionGroup");
2688 return;
2689 }
2690
2691 // We enabled automatic media selection because we want alternate audio tracks to be enabled/disabled automatically,
2692 // but set the selected legible track to nil so text tracks will not be automatically configured.
2693 if (!m_textTracks.size())
2694 [m_avPlayerItem.get() selectMediaOption:nil inMediaSelectionGroup:safeMediaSelectionGroupForLegibleMedia()];
2695
2696 Vector<RefPtr<InbandTextTrackPrivateAVF>> removedTextTracks = m_textTracks;
2697 NSArray *legibleOptions = [PAL::getAVMediaSelectionGroupClass() playableMediaSelectionOptionsFromArray:[legibleGroup options]];
2698 for (AVMediaSelectionOption *option in legibleOptions) {
2699 bool newTrack = true;
2700 for (unsigned i = removedTextTracks.size(); i > 0; --i) {
2701 if (removedTextTracks[i - 1]->textTrackCategory() == InbandTextTrackPrivateAVF::LegacyClosedCaption)
2702 continue;
2703
2704 RetainPtr<AVMediaSelectionOption> currentOption;
2705#if ENABLE(AVF_CAPTIONS)
2706 if (removedTextTracks[i - 1]->textTrackCategory() == InbandTextTrackPrivateAVF::OutOfBand) {
2707 RefPtr<OutOfBandTextTrackPrivateAVF> track = static_cast<OutOfBandTextTrackPrivateAVF*>(removedTextTracks[i - 1].get());
2708 currentOption = track->mediaSelectionOption();
2709 } else
2710#endif
2711 {
2712 RefPtr<InbandTextTrackPrivateAVFObjC> track = static_cast<InbandTextTrackPrivateAVFObjC*>(removedTextTracks[i - 1].get());
2713 currentOption = track->mediaSelectionOption();
2714 }
2715
2716 if ([currentOption.get() isEqual:option]) {
2717 removedTextTracks.remove(i - 1);
2718 newTrack = false;
2719 break;
2720 }
2721 }
2722 if (!newTrack)
2723 continue;
2724
2725#if ENABLE(AVF_CAPTIONS)
2726 if ([option outOfBandSource]) {
2727 m_textTracks.append(OutOfBandTextTrackPrivateAVF::create(this, option));
2728 m_textTracks.last()->setHasBeenReported(true); // Ignore out-of-band tracks that we passed to AVFoundation so we do not double-count them
2729 continue;
2730 }
2731#endif
2732
2733 m_textTracks.append(InbandTextTrackPrivateAVFObjC::create(this, option, InbandTextTrackPrivate::CueFormat::Generic));
2734 }
2735
2736 processNewAndRemovedTextTracks(removedTextTracks);
2737}

2798String MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack() const
2799{
2800 if (!m_languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack.isNull())
2801 return m_languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack;
2802
2803 if (!m_avPlayerItem.get())
2804 return emptyString();
2805
2806 // If AVFoundation has an audible group, return the language of the currently selected audible option.
2807 AVMediaSelectionGroup *audibleGroup = [m_avAsset.get() mediaSelectionGroupForMediaCharacteristic:AVMediaCharacteristicAudible];
2808 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_BEGIN
2809 AVMediaSelectionOption *currentlySelectedAudibleOption = [m_avPlayerItem.get() selectedMediaOptionInMediaSelectionGroup:audibleGroup];
2810 ALLOW_DEPRECATED_DECLARATIONS_END
2811 if (currentlySelectedAudibleOption) {
2812 m_languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack = [[currentlySelectedAudibleOption locale] localeIdentifier];
2813 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "language of selected audible option ", m_languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack);
2814
2815 return m_languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack;
2816 }
2817
2818 // AVFoundation synthesizes an audible group when there is only one ungrouped audio track if there is also a legible group (one or
2819 // more in-band text tracks). It doesn't know about out-of-band tracks, so if there is a single audio track return its language.
2820 NSArray *tracks = [m_avAsset.get() tracksWithMediaType:AVMediaTypeAudio];
2821 if (!tracks || [tracks count] != 1) {
2822 m_languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack = emptyString();
2823 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, tracks ? [tracks count] : 0, " audio tracks, returning empty");
2824 return m_languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack;
2825 }
2826
2827 AVAssetTrack *track = [tracks objectAtIndex:0];
2828 m_languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack = AVTrackPrivateAVFObjCImpl::languageForAVAssetTrack(track);
2829
2830 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "single audio track has language \"", m_languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack, "\"");
2831
2832 return m_languageOfPrimaryAudioTrack;
2833}

2904static NSString *exernalDeviceDisplayNameForPlayer(AVPlayer *player)
2905{
2906#if HAVE(CELESTIAL)
2907 if (!PAL::isAVFoundationFrameworkAvailable())
2908 return nil;
2909
2910 if (auto context = PAL::OutputContext::sharedAudioPresentationOutputContext())
2911 return context->deviceName();
2912
2913 if (player.externalPlaybackType != AVPlayerExternalPlaybackTypeAirPlay)
2914 return nil;
2915
2916 auto pickableRoutes = adoptCF(MRMediaRemoteCopyPickableRoutes());
2917 if (!pickableRoutes || !CFArrayGetCount(pickableRoutes.get()))
2918 return nil;
2919
2920 NSString *displayName = nil;
2921 for (NSDictionary *pickableRoute in (__bridge NSArray *)pickableRoutes.get()) {
2922 if (![pickableRoute[AVController_RouteDescriptionKey_RouteCurrentlyPicked] boolValue])
2923 continue;
2924
2925 displayName = pickableRoute[AVController_RouteDescriptionKey_RouteName];
2926
2927 NSString *routeName = pickableRoute[AVController_RouteDescriptionKey_AVAudioRouteName];
2928 if (![routeName isEqualToString:@"Speaker"] && ![routeName isEqualToString:@"HDMIOutput"])
2929 break;
2930
2931 // The route is a speaker or HDMI out, override the name to be the localized device model.
2932 NSString *localizedDeviceModelName = localizedDeviceModel();
2933
2934 // In cases where a route with that name already exists, prefix the name with the model.
2935 BOOL includeLocalizedDeviceModelName = NO;
2936 for (NSDictionary *otherRoute in (__bridge NSArray *)pickableRoutes.get()) {
2937 if (otherRoute == pickableRoute)
2938 continue;
2939
2940 if ([otherRoute[AVController_RouteDescriptionKey_RouteName] rangeOfString:displayName].location != NSNotFound) {
2941 includeLocalizedDeviceModelName = YES;
2942 break;
2943 }
2944 }
2945
2946 if (includeLocalizedDeviceModelName)
2947 displayName = [NSString stringWithFormat:@"%@ %@", localizedDeviceModelName, displayName];
2948 else
2949 displayName = localizedDeviceModelName;
2950
2951 break;
2952 }
2953
2954 return displayName;
2955#else
2956 UNUSED_PARAM(player);
2957 return nil;
2958#endif
2959}

3158void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::setBufferingPolicy(MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy policy)
3159{
3160 ALWAYS_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, policy);
3161
3162 if (m_bufferingPolicy == policy)
3163 return;
3164
3165 m_bufferingPolicy = policy;
3166
3167 if (!m_avPlayer)
3168 return;
3169
3170#if HAVE(AVPLAYER_RESOURCE_CONSERVATION_LEVEL)
3171 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy::Default) == AVPlayerResourceConservationLevelNone, "MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy::Default is not AVPlayerResourceConservationLevelNone as expected");
3172 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy::LimitReadAhead) == AVPlayerResourceConservationLevelReduceReadAhead, "MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy::LimitReadAhead is not AVPlayerResourceConservationLevelReduceReadAhead as expected");
3173 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy::MakeResourcesPurgeable) == AVPlayerResourceConservationLevelReuseActivePlayerResources, "MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy::MakeResourcesPurgeable is not AVPlayerResourceConservationLevelReuseActivePlayerResources as expected");
3174 static_assert(static_cast<size_t>(MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy::PurgeResources) == AVPlayerResourceConservationLevelRecycleBuffer, "MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy::PurgeResources is not AVPlayerResourceConservationLevelRecycleBuffer as expected");
3175
3176 if ([m_avPlayer respondsToSelector:@selector(setResourceConservationLevelWhilePaused:)]) {
3177 m_avPlayer.get().resourceConservationLevelWhilePaused = static_cast<AVPlayerResourceConservationLevel>(policy);
3178 updateStates();
3179 return;
3180 }
3181#endif
3182
3183 switch (policy) {
3184 case MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy::Default:
3185 setAVPlayerItem(m_avPlayerItem.get());
3186 break;
3187 case MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy::LimitReadAhead:
3188 case MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy::MakeResourcesPurgeable:
3189 setAVPlayerItem(nil);
3190 break;
3191 case MediaPlayer::BufferingPolicy::PurgeResources:
3192 setAVPlayerItem(nil);
3193 setAVPlayerItem(m_avPlayerItem.get());
3194 break;
3195 }
3196
3197 updateStates();
3198}

3227void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::metadataGroupDidArrive(const RetainPtr<NSArray>& groups, const MediaTime& currentTime)
3228{
3229 for (AVDateRangeMetadataGroup *group in groups.get()) {
3230 auto groupStartDate = group.startDate.timeIntervalSince1970;
3231 auto groupEndDate = group.endDate.timeIntervalSince1970;
3232 auto groupDuration = MediaTime::createWithDouble(groupEndDate - groupStartDate);
3233
3234 // A manifest without a #EXT-X-PROGRAM-DATE-TIME won't have a start date, so if currentDate
3235 // is zero assume the metadata items start at the beginning of the stream.
3236 double groupStartTime = 0;
3237 if (auto currentDate = m_avPlayerItem.get().currentDate.timeIntervalSince1970)
3238 groupStartTime = groupStartDate - currentDate - currentTime.toDouble();
3239
3240 auto groupCopy = adoptNS([[NSMutableArray alloc] init]);
3241 for (AVMetadataItem *item in group.items) {
3242 RetainPtr<AVMutableMetadataItem> itemCopy = adoptNS([item mutableCopy]);
3243 if (!CMTIME_IS_VALID(itemCopy.get().time))
3244 itemCopy.get().time = PAL::CMTimeMakeWithSeconds(groupStartTime, MediaTime::DefaultTimeScale);
3245 if (!CMTIME_IS_VALID(itemCopy.get().duration))
3246 itemCopy.get().duration = PAL::toCMTime(groupDuration);
3247 [groupCopy addObject:itemCopy.get()];
3248 }
3249
3250 metadataDidArrive(groupCopy, currentTime);
3251 }
3252}
3253
3254void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::metadataDidArrive(const RetainPtr<NSArray>& metadata, const MediaTime& mediaTime)
3255{
3256 m_currentMetaData = metadata && ![metadata isKindOfClass:[NSNull class]] ? metadata : nil;
3257
3258 INFO_LOG(LOGIDENTIFIER, "adding ", m_currentMetaData ? [m_currentMetaData.get() count] : 0, " at time ", mediaTime);
3259
3260#if ENABLE(DATACUE_VALUE)
3261 if (seeking())
3262 return;
3263
3264 if (!m_metadataTrack)
3265 processMetadataTrack();
3266
3267 if (!metadata || [metadata isKindOfClass:[NSNull class]]) {
3268 m_metadataTrack->updatePendingCueEndTimes(mediaTime);
3269 return;
3270 }
3271
3272 // Set the duration of all incomplete cues before adding new ones.
3273 MediaTime earliestStartTime = MediaTime::positiveInfiniteTime();
3274 for (AVMetadataItem *item in m_currentMetaData.get()) {
3275 MediaTime start = std::max(PAL::toMediaTime(item.time), MediaTime::zeroTime());
3276 if (start < earliestStartTime)
3277 earliestStartTime = start;
3278 }
3279 m_metadataTrack->updatePendingCueEndTimes(earliestStartTime);
3280
3281 for (AVMetadataItem *item in m_currentMetaData.get()) {
3282 MediaTime start;
3283 if (CMTIME_IS_VALID(item.time))
3284 start = std::max(PAL::toMediaTime(item.time), MediaTime::zeroTime());
3285
3286 MediaTime end = MediaTime::positiveInfiniteTime();
3287 auto duration = item.duration;
3288 if (CMTIME_IS_VALID(duration) && PAL::CMTimeGetSeconds(duration) > 0.001)
3289 end = start + PAL::toMediaTime(duration);
3290
3291 AtomString type = nullAtom();
3292 if (item.keySpace)
3293 type = metadataType(item.keySpace);
3294
3295 m_metadataTrack->addDataCue(start, end, SerializedPlatformDataCue::create({ WebCore::SerializedPlatformDataCueValue::PlatformType::ObjC, item }), type);
3296 }
3297#endif
3298}

3300void MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundationObjC::tracksDidChange(const RetainPtr<NSArray>& tracks)
3301{
3302 for (AVPlayerItemTrack *track in m_cachedTracks.get())
3303 [track removeObserver:m_objcObserver.get() forKeyPath:@"enabled"];

3305 NSArray *assetTracks = [m_avAsset tracks];
3306
3307 m_cachedTracks = [tracks objectsAtIndexes:[tracks indexesOfObjectsPassingTest:^(id obj, NSUInteger, BOOL*) {
3308 AVAssetTrack* assetTrack = [obj assetTrack];
3309
3310 if ([assetTracks containsObject:assetTrack])
3311 return YES;

3314 if (!hasLoadedMediaSelectionGroups())

3318 return NO;

3327 }]];

3613- (void)observeValueForKeyPath:keyPath ofObject:(id)object change:(NSDictionary *)change context:(MediaPlayerAVFoundationObservationContext)context
3614{
3615 ensureOnMainThread([self, strongSelf = retainPtr(self), keyPath = retainPtr(keyPath), change = retainPtr(change), object = retainPtr(object), context]() mutable {
3616 if (!m_player)
3617 return;
3618
3619 m_player->queueTaskOnEventLoop([player = m_player, keyPath = WTFMove(keyPath), change = WTFMove(change), object = WTFMove(object), context] {
3620 if (!player)
3621 return;
3622
3623 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
3624
3625 id newValue = [change valueForKey:NSKeyValueChangeNewKey];
3626 bool willChange = [[change valueForKey:NSKeyValueChangeNotificationIsPriorKey] boolValue];
3627 bool shouldLogValue = !willChange;
3628
3629 if (context == MediaPlayerAVFoundationObservationContextAVPlayerLayer) {
3630 if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"readyForDisplay"])
3631 player->firstFrameAvailableDidChange([newValue boolValue]);
3632 }
3633
3634 if (context == MediaPlayerAVFoundationObservationContextPlayerItemTrack) {
3635 if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"enabled"])
3636 player->trackEnabledDidChange([newValue boolValue]);
3637 }
3638
3639 if (context == MediaPlayerAVFoundationObservationContextPlayerItem && willChange) {
3640 if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"playbackLikelyToKeepUp"])
3641 player->playbackLikelyToKeepUpWillChange();
3642 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"playbackBufferEmpty"])
3643 player->playbackBufferEmptyWillChange();
3644 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"playbackBufferFull"])
3645 player->playbackBufferFullWillChange();
3646 }
3647
3648 if (context == MediaPlayerAVFoundationObservationContextPlayerItem && !willChange) {
3649 // A value changed for an AVPlayerItem
3650 if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"status"])
3651 player->playerItemStatusDidChange([newValue intValue]);
3652 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"playbackLikelyToKeepUp"])
3653 player->playbackLikelyToKeepUpDidChange([newValue boolValue]);
3654 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"playbackBufferEmpty"])
3655 player->playbackBufferEmptyDidChange([newValue boolValue]);
3656 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"playbackBufferFull"])
3657 player->playbackBufferFullDidChange([newValue boolValue]);
3658 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"asset"]) {
3659 player->setAsset(RetainPtr<id>(newValue));
3660 shouldLogValue = false;
3661 } else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"loadedTimeRanges"])
3662 player->loadedTimeRangesDidChange(RetainPtr<NSArray>(newValue));
3663 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"seekableTimeRanges"])
3664 player->seekableTimeRangesDidChange(RetainPtr<NSArray>(newValue));
3665 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"tracks"]) {
3666 player->tracksDidChange(RetainPtr<NSArray>(newValue));
3667 shouldLogValue = false;
3668 } else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"hasEnabledAudio"])
3669 player->hasEnabledAudioDidChange([newValue boolValue]);
3670 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"presentationSize"])
3671 player->presentationSizeDidChange(FloatSize([newValue sizeValue]));
3672 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"duration"])
3673 player->durationDidChange(PAL::toMediaTime([newValue CMTimeValue]));
3674 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"canPlayFastReverse"])
3675 player->canPlayFastReverseDidChange([newValue boolValue]);
3676 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"canPlayFastForward"])
3677 player->canPlayFastForwardDidChange([newValue boolValue]);
3678 }
3679
3680 if (context == MediaPlayerAVFoundationObservationContextPlayer && !willChange) {
3681 // A value changed for an AVPlayer.
3682 if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"rate"])
3683 player->rateDidChange([newValue doubleValue]);
3684 else if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"timeControlStatus"])
3685 player->timeControlStatusDidChange([newValue intValue]);

3692 player->outputObscuredDueToInsufficientExternalProtectionChanged([newValue boolValue]);

3694 }

3696 if (player->logger().willLog(player->logChannel(), WTFLogLevel::Debug) && !([keyPath isEqualToString:@"loadedTimeRanges"] || [keyPath isEqualToString:@"seekableTimeRanges"])) {
3697 auto identifier = Logger::LogSiteIdentifier("MediaPlayerPrivateAVFoundation", "observeValueForKeyPath", player->logIdentifier());
3698
3699 if (shouldLogValue) {
3700 if ([keyPath isEqualToString:@"duration"])
3701 player->logger().debug(player->logChannel(), identifier, "did change '", [keyPath UTF8String], "' to ", PAL::toMediaTime([newValue CMTimeValue]));
3702 else {

3704 player->logger().debug(player->logChannel(), identifier, "did change '", [keyPath UTF8String], "' to ", [valueString.get() UTF8String]);
3705 }

3709 });
3710 });
